The second task is to
  - Add an npm script as a shortcut to a Sequelize migrate command
    - This is to avoid having to install Sequelize globally
 
6 - Exercise 2 Solution
Example Syntax
  uglify: {
    my_target: {
      files: {
        'public/app.js': 'public/app.js'
      }
    }
  }
  
  grunt.loadNpmTasks('grunt-contrib-uglify');
  


                    Section 3 - The Database
1 - Sequelize & PostgreSQL
This section will cover how to use a relational db with NodeJS
There will 2 databases used 
  - Sequelize
    - It is the most feature rich ORM in NodeJS
    - It has a promise based interface
    - It has support for migrations
    - There is however a smaller community and few resources
  - PostgreSql
    - This is feature rich and performant
    - It can be used with Amazon RDS
Isn't SQL for Old people
  - NoSql database support is better in NodeJS
  - There are a couple of main reasons for choosing SQL
    - Postgres is an excellent piece of software
    - RDS from Amazon is also very very good

2 - The Database Code Demo
A code walkthrough of the database section of the sample app
Example Syntax
  // sequelizerc file
    // Default config file for sequelize
    const path = require('path');

    module.exports = {
      config: path.resolve('db', 'database.js'),
      'migrations-path': path.resolve('db', 'migrations'),
      'models-path': path.resolve('src', 'server', 'models')
    } 
  
  // Database.js file in db folder
    // The sample app configuration lives in the ../config file
    // Sequelize requires database configuation information to be specified in a certain way
    // This is not congruent with other configuration in the sample app
    const config = require('../config');

    // The configuration object for sequelize migrations, they are configured elsewhere based on the NODE_ENV settings
    let sequelizeConfig = {
      url: config.databaseUrl,
      dialect: 'postgres'
    }
    sequelizeConfig.production = sequelizeConfig;
    sequelizeConfig.test = sequelizeConfig;
    sequelizeConfig.development = sequelizeConfig;

    // Export the final database config file
    module.exports = sequelizeConfig;
Migrations and the migration system is similar to other databases
  - There is a timestamp as part of the file name which is an identifier

3 - Alternative Databases
The main recommended alternative is MongoDB
  - It natively speaks JSON
  - It is very fast and there are no migrations
  - Mongoose, the ODM layer on MongoDB is probably the best tool of its type on Node

