5 - Exercise 3 Solution Part 1
The first thing to be done when wanting to update a data model is to generate a migration
Example Syntax
  // To generate a migration using Sequelize -- sequelize migration:create
  // This will create a new migration file, a migration will consist of 2 operations, Up & Down
  // When modifying a database from its previous state this will go in the Up operation, any rollbacks in the Down
  'use strict';
  
  module.exports = {
    up: function(queryInterface, Sequelize){
      // Contains any altering commands
      // Adding a column to an existing db
      queryInterface.addColumn(
        'Todos',                      // Name of the table
        'completed',                  // Name of the attribute/column
        Sequelize.BOOLEAN             // Data types
      )
    }
    
    down: function(queryInterface, Sequelize){
      // Contains reverting commands
      queryInterface.removeColumn(
        'Todos',                       
        'completed'
      )
    }
  }
The instructor uses Postico
  - https://eggerapps.at/postico/
  - It is a PostgreSQL client but only for Mac
To perform the database migration
  - sequelize db:migrate

